WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
(progressive house music)

00:00:11.150 --> 00:00:12.850
- The science behind X3

00:00:13.895 --> 00:00:16.200
there's actually 16 studies.

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:18.273
Those are all in the book.

00:00:19.210 --> 00:00:22.150
There's new studies on variable
resistance all the time.

00:00:22.150 --> 00:00:23.820
And I think it's really important

00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:26.230
that we point to studies
that we didn't do.

00:00:26.230 --> 00:00:28.280
These were all third parties, people,

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:31.370
some of the researchers
I've met at conferences

00:00:31.370 --> 00:00:32.920
and most of them I haven't.

00:00:32.920 --> 00:00:36.370
So all of these 16 studies
came to the same conclusion.

00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:39.020
Now, some of them use
different combinations

00:00:39.020 --> 00:00:42.930
or different weight
apparatus, plus banding.

00:00:42.930 --> 00:00:47.930
It doesn't really matter if
you're holding X weight here,

00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:52.080
and 1.5X weight here that is better

00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:54.190
than holding one static weight.

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:58.630
Now we have X here and just about 5X here.

00:00:58.630 --> 00:00:59.870
So

00:00:59.870 --> 00:01:03.080
that's a more aggressive level

00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:05.750
of variable resistance.

00:01:05.750 --> 00:01:08.030
And you'll read in some of those studies

00:01:08.030 --> 00:01:09.810
that the

00:01:09.810 --> 00:01:11.560
degree of variance

00:01:11.560 --> 00:01:13.060
as it becomes higher,

00:01:13.060 --> 00:01:14.680
the growth rate becomes higher.

00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:17.500
And that's why that decision was made.

00:01:17.500 --> 00:01:20.430
So there's 16 studies in the book.

00:01:20.430 --> 00:01:22.350
There's about six on the website

00:01:22.350 --> 00:01:24.750
cause we wanted to keep it very readable.

00:01:24.750 --> 00:01:28.960
I also want to talk about
one study that found

00:01:28.960 --> 00:01:31.870
that variable resistance doesn't work.

00:01:31.870 --> 00:01:34.740
So it went against the 16 other studies.

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:36.770
And I want to explain that one.

00:01:36.770 --> 00:01:40.360
So this had a weight training
group as the control,

00:01:40.360 --> 00:01:42.760
and then it had a
variable resistance group

00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:44.910
that was training with just bands.

00:01:44.910 --> 00:01:47.640
So no bar, no nothing just bands.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:50.810
And after we were puzzled by this study,

00:01:50.810 --> 00:01:53.800
because how could a study
on variable resistance

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:56.060
go against the 16 other studies?

00:01:56.060 --> 00:01:58.960
So it turns out they used a TheraBand

00:01:58.960 --> 00:02:02.160
and that's a rehab type product.

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:04.670
And we found a specific model of TheraBand

00:02:04.670 --> 00:02:07.210
in the method section of this study.

00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:10.160
And it showed that the
highest possible resistance

00:02:10.160 --> 00:02:15.160
they could have gotten to at
peak force was 14.1 pounds.

00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:17.450
So this was a study that was written,

00:02:17.450 --> 00:02:20.060
so the variable resistance failed.

00:02:20.060 --> 00:02:22.130
But yeah, it was

00:02:23.290 --> 00:02:25.510
very misleading,

00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:28.169
but the rest of them have
very powerful results.

00:02:28.169 --> 00:02:29.840
And as I mentioned,

00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:32.150
the more aggressive level of the variance,

00:02:32.150 --> 00:02:34.130
the more aggressive level of growth,

00:02:34.130 --> 00:02:37.730
and that is why X3 is the

00:02:37.730 --> 00:02:38.870
highest degree

00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:41.360
of variance that anyone's
ever really used.

00:02:41.360 --> 00:02:45.930
And there's hardly any
variable resistance products

00:02:45.930 --> 00:02:46.890
even out there.

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:48.470
And the ones that are out there

00:02:48.470 --> 00:02:50.240
will have something like X here,

00:02:50.240 --> 00:02:52.110
and 1.2X here,

00:02:52.110 --> 00:02:53.490
and, you know,

00:02:53.490 --> 00:02:54.513
kind of meaningless.

